Manchester City have announced that defender, Jose Angelino has left the club on loan to join Red Bull Leipzig until the end of the season. Angelino, 23, played just 12 times for Pep Guardiola’s side this season. Man City made this known in a statement on their official website on Friday. “Angelino will spend the rest of the season on loan at Red Bull Leipzig. “The Spanish wing-back has played 12 times for City this season after re-joining the Club from PSV Eindhoven in the summer. “With City’s injury problems clearing up over the past few weeks, Angelino will have more opportunity for senior football with the Bundesliga side during his loan move. “Everyone as the Club wishes Angelino good luck for the remainder of the campaign,” a club statement read.